{
  "stem": "6554.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were taking out Jews from trains, and they were shooting them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They used to be the [POLISH], that used to be the-- a Polish [POLISH] army.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they did not like Jews, either.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So there was a big pogrom in Keltz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They killed, I think, maybe about 50 Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so we said, we have to get out of Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It took a while.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was a lot of organization.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were shipping Jews to Israel and to Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Finally, they told us we can go over the border at night from Poland to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "From Czechoslovakia, we went to Austria.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And from Austria, we went to Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When we were crossing the borders, they say that we are Greeks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We are not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We are Greeks.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because at that time, they let the Greek citizen out from Poland to go back to Greece because it was, at that time, I think it was a revolution in Greece or something.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And when we came to Germany, they send all transport to Ulm.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In Ulm, there was about five DP lagers Jewish, and there was one Polish larger for Polish non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And there was one Ukrainian lager.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we stayed in-- in Germany since '46 till 1949.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In 1949, we received papers for my auntie from Detroit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we had to go to Bremerhaven and wait for a ship to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We came to Bremerhaven and the ship was US Marine Merlin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was a military ship.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then-- then they loaded us up on the ship and we arrived in New York June 16, 1949.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My auntie's son, his name was Bernard Weissman, he came over and he picked us up from the ship.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And he took us with the train to Detroit.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
